		<encodingDesc>
			<projectDesc><p>David Livingstone writes his diary entries over a portion of a page from The Standard (London). Livingstone's "overtext" is what is transcribed and represented in Text Encoding Initiative (TEI) P5 XML encoding. In addition, this folio includes the number "34" written in pencil in the upper right-hand corner of the page in a second, unknown hand. Finally, the folio also includes two slashes in red crayon(?) near the top center the page in a third, unknown hand (possibly Horace Waller's). These slashes mark the top of a newspaper article in the "undertext" that describes the arrival of a letter from Livingstone dated 13 May 1869.</p>
